oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Land indenture between Alexander Simpson and Michael Dunn
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Deed conveying 272 and one-half acres of land in Davidson County from Alexander Simpson to Michael C. Dunn at the sum of $3,270. The land, later known as Grassmere, was situated "on the waters of the west fork of Mill Creek."
The parcel of land represented in this deed was originally part of 640 acres granted to William Simpson, Alexander Simpson's father, by North Carolina under land grant number 174 in 1786.
